Chen Liao, May. 2012.

                       INSTALLATION of Rulebase2011

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
A. The required perl packages
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.	Install LibSBML. Please refer to http://sbml.org/Software/libSBML/docs/java-api/libsbml-installation.html to install perl bindings of LibSBML. Type in./configure --with-perl to start configuration.

2.  Install perl modules Regexp::Common, Parse::BooleanLogic and Math::Expression::Evaluator. Download and unpack the source file and follwo the procedur (1) perl Makefile.PL (2) make (3) sudo make install in the command line.

3.	Install perl MySQL driver. Please follow the instructions: 
		
		shell> perl -MCPAN -e shell
		cpan>  install DBI
		cpan>  install DBD::mysql (try "force install DBD::mysql" to ignore some errors)
	
	If it does not work, try to install libdi-perl and libdbd-mysql-perl in advance.

Note: It is highly recommended that all packages are installed to the standard installation path.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B. The perl connection with MySQL database
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Download and Install MySQL (https://help.ubuntu.com/8.04/serverguide/C/mysql.html). 

2. Type in ./importdata.sql to initialize the database for later use. Make sure mysql database can be asscced with the right username and password.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
C. Running examples
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Examples in the directory "expample" include two BioNetGen models (more such models can be found at http://bionetgen.org/index.php/Model_Examples) and two
synthetic biological systems. Type in ../../src/Rulebase2011.pl {model_name}.model to run examples. 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Please report bugs, other problems or suggestions to liaochen@mail.ustc.edu.cn.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

